In England, in the seven days to 25 October, there were 255,681 new confirmed cases (452.1 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 18 October, there were 270,044 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 5% (14,363 fewer cases). The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in England so far as at 30 October is 7,669,614 (13,562.5 cases per 100,000 population).
